title: Appointments to Advisory Council on Food and Environmental Hygiene announced
content_text:
p>
    The Government today (March 25) announced that the Chief Executive had 
    re-appointed Mr Felix Fong Wo as the Chairman of the Advisory Council on 
    Food and Environmental Hygiene for a term of two years with effect from 
    April 1, 2011. Mr Fong is a lawyer and has been the chairman of the advisory 
    council since 2009.  Meanwhile, 14 serving non-official members were also re-appointed and a new 
    non-official member, Mrs Sandra Mak Wong Siu-chun, was appointed. All the

appointments are for a term of two years from April 1, 2011, to March 31, 
    2013. Mrs Mak is the chief executive officer of A-World Consulting Limited and has 
    extensive experience in public relations and corporate communications. She 
    has served on other government advisory boards and committees.  Welcoming the new appointment, the Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York 
    Chow, said: "Mrs Mak has been taking a leading role in her profession. I am 
    confident that she will contribute to the deliberations of the council by

confident that she will contribute to the deliberations of the council by 
    considering food safety and environmental hygiene issues from a broad public 
    interest perspective and provide valuable advice to assist the Government in 
    formulating the relevant policies." Dr Chow also expressed his gratitude to the outgoing member, Dr Lo Chi-kin, 
    for his professional advice and significant contribution to the advisory 
    council.  The advisory council is a non-statutory body established on April 1, 2000, 
    to advise the Government on food and environmental hygiene issues. Its terms

to advise the Government on food and environmental hygiene issues. Its terms 
    of reference are - * To consider and advise the Secretary for Food and Health on policies 
    relating to food safety, environmental hygiene and veterinary public health, 
    and to monitor their implementation; * To advise the Secretary for Food and Health on the regulation of farms, 
    food premises, food hazards and food composition; * To receive reports on the handling of major food and farm incidents; and * To advise the Secretary for Food and Health on community education and 
    publicity programmes for promoting public understanding of food safety and

publicity programmes for promoting public understanding of food safety and public responsibility for environmental hygiene.
